There are also <a href="https://userresearch.blog.gov.uk/cross-government-user-research-meetups/" target="_blank"> cross-government communities</a> that publish blog content and hold meetups. 

## Community meetups

If you are a user researcher (civil servant and contractor) at DfE, you are invited and encouraged to attend our community meetups: regular sessions where user researchers come together in person, or remotely using Teams.

We have monthly national meetups, run remotely, and each DfE office location with digital staff has a local meetup, run as a hybrid session: people are encouraged to attend in-person, but can join using Teams.

The content of meetings differs depending on which you attend, and each local community has its way of doing things, and its own personality.

| __National__  | __Local__ |
|---------------|---------------|
| Share knowledge and skills within the community and with other professions      | Share experience and support with researchers in that area |
| Discuss challenges and best practices relevant to the whole community      | Discuss things related explicitly to researchers in each locale |

| __Area__ | __Frequency__ | __Organisers__ |
|---------------|---------------|----------------
| __National__ | First Thursday of the month, 1-2 pm | Chardai Brice |
| __Coventry and Bristol__ |  | Kate O'Leary |
| __London__ | Third Thursday of the month, 1-2 pm | Valentina Mazzi, Costa Christou |
| __Manchester and Sheffield__ | Third Thursday of the month, 1-2 pm | Rachael Sumner, James Angove |

If your office doesn't have a local community, please contact Keisha Herbert to discuss which local community would be best for you to join.

Some sessions are recorded to give everyone in the community a chance to access the content. <a href="https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1wRa-XyazD55s_Vnk8fjC9S4VnMi9JQFi?usp=share_link" target="_blank"> Watch recordings of previous meetups</a>.

## Getting involved

Becoming an active member is a good way of shaping how your local community does things.  

There is a <a href="working-groups-and-interest-groups.html">community of practice working group</a>, which develops our community strategy, and plans content for national meetups. Each local community has a community lead or team to plan the sessions.

If you'd like to present at a national meeting or being a part of the working group, contact <a href="https://ukgovernmentdfe.slack.com/team/U0351HD3WER">Chardai Brice</a> to learn more about how the team can support you to deliver a great session or steer the future of national meetups.

